	</form></div><span class="pb doctop" title="page number in print edition" id="ADMS-06-14-02-pb-0308">308<a style="padding-left: 5px" onclick="window.open('/img-document-get.xqy?image=ADMS/Pages/ADMS-06-14/ADMS-06-14-02-pb-0308.jpg', 'pageImage', 'scrollbars=1,resizable=1'); return false" onkeypress="this.onclick();" tabindex="0" title="Click to view image of page from print edition"><img src="/img-ML/page-icon.gif" width="18" height="20" style="vertical-align:middle;" alt="page icon"/></a></span><div class="doc">

<h1>From Philippe Jean Joseph Lagau</h1>
<div class="docbody" xml:lang="fra">
<div class="opener"><table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationLeft">Monsieur</td>
		<td class="salutationRight">a hambourg ce 3 mars 1783</td>
	      </tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>Cest avec le plus sensible plaisir que jai lhonneur de vous annoncer que Monsieur Votre fils sest embarqu  Copenhague pour Kiel dou Il se rendra  hambourg ou nous Lattendons incessament.<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0203-fn-0001" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0203-fn-0001-ptr">1</a> Monsieur le Chevalier de Viviers Ministre du Roy en cette ville<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0203-fn-0002" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0203-fn-0002-ptr">2</a> se fait un plaisir de faire sa Connoissance et je ne manquerai pas de lui temoigner tout mon empressement  lui tre util, pour Convaincre Votre Excellence du zle que jai  vous Convaincre du profond respect avec lequel jai Lhonneur detre / Monsieur / de Votre Excellence / Le trs humble et trs obeissant Serviteur</p>
<div class="closer"><p class="signed">Lagau</p>
</div></div>
<div class="translation">
<h2><span class="hi-all-small-caps" style="font-variant: small-caps; text-transform: lowercase;">Translation</span></h2>
<div class="opener"><table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationLeft">Sir</td>
		<td class="salutationRight">Hamburg, 3 March 1783</td>
	      </tr>
      </table>
</div>
<p>It gives me great pleasure to inform you that your son has embarked at Copenhagen for Kiel, whence he will travel to Hamburg, where we await <span class="pb" title="page number in print edition" id="ADMS-06-14-02-pb-0309">[309<a style="padding-left: 0px" onclick="window.open('/img-document-get.xqy?image=ADMS/Pages/ADMS-06-14/ADMS-06-14-02-pb-0309.jpg', 'pageImage', 'scrollbars=1,resizable=1'); return false" onkeypress="this.onclick();" tabindex="0" title="Click to view image of page from print edition"><img src="/img-ML/page-icon.gif" width="18" height="20" style="vertical-align:middle;" alt="page icon"/></a>]</span>him forthwith.<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0203-fn-0001" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0203-fn-0001-ptr">1</a> The Chevalier de Viviers, the kings minister to this town,<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0203-fn-0002" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0203-fn-0002-ptr">2</a> will be happy to make his acquaintance, and I myself shall not fail to express my eagerness to assist him, the better to convince your excellency of the deep respect with which I have the honor to be, sir, your excellencys very humble and very obedient servant</p>
<div class="closer"><p class="signed">Lagau</p>
</div></div>
<div class="docback">
<div class="note-source" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0203-sn">
   <p><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ recipients copy (A recipients copy is assumed to be in the hand of the signer unless it is otherwise described.) ]">RC</abbr> (<span class="ref-terms">Adams Papers</span>).</p>
</div>
        <div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0203-fn-0001-ptr" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0203-fn-0001">1</a>
   <p><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Quincy Adams (17671848), son of John and Abigail Adams ]">JQA</abbr> reached Copenhagen on 15 Feb., intending to sail from there to Kiel. But contrary winds and harbor ice forced him to abandon that plan, with the result that he departed Copenhagen on 5 March, traveled overland to Hamburg, andalthough his diary indicates the 10tharrived there on the evening of the 11th. Lagaus information about <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Quincy Adams (17671848), son of John and Abigail Adams ]">JQA</abbr>s planned departure from Copenhagen was derived from a letter to the French minister at Hamburg written by Matthieu de Basquiat, Baron de La Houze, the French minister at Copenhagen, whom <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Quincy Adams (17671848), son of John and Abigail Adams ]">JQA</abbr> had seen on 19, 23, and 24 Feb. (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;Diary of John Quincy Adams&lt;/i&gt;, ed. David Grayson Allen, Robert J. Taylor, and others, Cambridge, 1981. ]">JQA, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Diary</span></span>, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-03-01-02-0005-0002-0009%20ADMS-print-03-01-02-0005-0002-0010%20ADMS-print-03-01-02-0005-0002-0011%20ADMS-print-03-01-02-0005-0002-0012#ADMS-03-01-02-pb-0171" class="pageNo">1:171174</a>; <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;Adams Family Correspondence&lt;/i&gt;, ed. L. H. Butterfield, Marc Friedlaender, Richard Alan Ryerson, Margaret A. Hogan, and others, Cambridge, 1963. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">AFC</span></span>, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-04-05-02-0053%20ADMS-print-04-05-02-0054#ADMS-04-05-02-pb-0097" class="pageNo">5:9798</a>, <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-04-05-02-0058%20ADMS-print-04-05-02-0059#ADMS-04-05-02-pb-0104" class="pageNo">104</a>; <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-14-02-0224" class="document">from Pierre Penet, 17 March</a>, below).</p>
</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#ADMS-06-14-02-0203-fn-0002-ptr" id="ADMS-06-14-02-0203-fn-0002">2</a>
   <p>Claude Antoine, Chevalier de Viviers, French minister to Hamburg since Oct. 1782, was the Comte de Vergennes brother-in-law (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Ludwig Bittner and others, eds., &lt;i&gt;Repertorium der diplomatischen Vertreter aller Lnder seit dem Westflischen Frieden&lt;/i&gt; (&lt;i&gt;1648&lt;/i&gt;), Oldenburg, 19361965; 3 vols. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Repertorium</span></span>, 3:119; <span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Orville T. Murphy, &lt;i&gt;Charles Gravier, Comte de Vergennes: French Diplomacy in the Age of Revolution, 17191787&lt;/i&gt;, Albany, 1982. ]">Murphy, <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Vergennes</span></span>, p. 167). For the ministers letter of 3 March to the Duc de La Vauguyon, which repeated Lagaus report on <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Quincy Adams (17671848), son of John and Abigail Adams ]">JQA</abbr>s movements at somewhat greater length, see <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-14-02-0216" class="document">Dumas letter of 11 March</a>, and note 1, below.</p>
</div></div>
</div><div class="citation_box"><div><span class="bold">Cite as: </span> 
